DOC.HEAD: NEW YORK: interest rates.
DOC.TEXT: The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell 2.13 to 2,709.26. Advancing issues were slightly ahead of decliners on the New York Stock Exchange, with 695 stocks rising, 675 falling and 550 unchanged. Big Board volume totaled a thin 77.61 million shares, against 120.98 million in the previous session. Many traders were extending the Christmas holiday weekend. The NYSE's composite index fell 0.23 to 191.72. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index slipped 0.04 to 370.84.
